Wires up the Mojo-driven home-tab swap that makes the Phase 8.1-8.4 port
panels actually reachable in the UI with sidecar data flowing.

layout.mojom:
- New ShowHomePanel(string panel_id) => (bool ok). Empty id returns to
  task-detail mode; unknown ids return ok=false (UI stays put).

SlayzoneBrowserView:
- New Mode enum {kTaskDetail, kHome}; mode_ defaults to kTaskDetail.
- kHomePanelIds allowlist: {automations, processes, test, git}. Typos
  reject at the host instead of silently loading a bogus chrome://.
- home_panel_webview_: lazy-created on first SetHomePanel(known_id);
  parented as BrowserView child overlaying the region grid. Bounds
  track GetLocalBounds() on resize.
- SetHomePanel(panel_id):
  * empty → hide home WebView, show region grid, mode_=kTaskDetail
  * known → LoadInitialURL(chrome://slayzone-<id>/), install RegionData
    on the home WebContents (so SlayzoneAutomationsUI etc. can resolve
    via FromRegionWebContents and bind the per-BrowserView Mojo host —
    this is the fix for the 'pipe closed' smoke failure), hide region
    grid, show home WebView, mode_=kHome
  * unknown → return false, no state change
- AddedToWidget parses --slayzone-home-panel=<id> for dev smoke.

SlayzoneLayoutHost::ShowHomePanel:
- Delegates to view_->SetHomePanel(panel_id), forwards the bool to the
  Mojo response. Callers (future panel-cycle UI in Phase 17) can render
  an inline error when ok=false.

Scope fences held — task-detail routing in SlayzoneRegionContainer
unchanged; per-region hosts + inline_tab_webview_ untouched. Additive
only.

Deliberate single-panel swap per approved plan Q2 deviation (multi-
visible side-by-side deferred to Phase 17 polish).
